nal Council oi Churches\nIS SPONSORING\nThe Fourth Annual\nNational Capital\nService: of Thanksgiving\nIn gratitude to God for the blessings of peace and plenty and for\nour privilege of shoring our abundonce with our neighbors in need\nAT\nThe Pint Baptist Church\n16th and O Streets N.W.\nSUNDAY, NOVEMBER 24,1957\n4:00-5:00 P.M.\nSPEAKER:\nU. LAWRENCE FOLKEMER\nMinister, Lutheran Church of the Reformation\nJust returned from an extensive world tour.\nOTHER PARTICIPANTS:\nDR. HENRY C. KOCH\nPresident, Council of Churches National Cap\nital Area\nMRS. GEORGE M. HAVERSTOCK\nPresident. United Church Women, Council\n0 of Churches NCA\nDR. EDWARD HUGHES FRUDEN\nPastor, First Baptist Church\nREV. ARTHUR F. ELMES\nPresident, Washington Ministerial Union\nDR. R. NORRIS WILSON\nExecutive Director, Church World Service\nDR. FRED S. BUSCHMEYER\nAssistant General Secretory, National Council\nof 'Churches\nSPECIAL DRAMATIC FEATURE by young people and foreign\nstudents.\nCHILIAN'S CHOIRS\nCHOIR OF FIRST BAPTIST CHURCH, WILLIAM WOODS, Director\nand Organist.\nINVITE GUESTS:\nNATIONAL GOVERNMENT LEADERS\nEMBASSY AND LEGATION REPRESENTATIVES\nNATIONAL CHURCH OFFICIALS\nThis Service of Thanksgiving Will Be Filmed For Newsreels and Television\nEPISCOPAL EPISCOPAL\nChrist Church Georgetown\nttSA,? s'm n n^e B v.-*n!S' aa o .'B:a!fflf\nAt Utitrtrb\u2019a Foxholl and Reservoir Roads\nfiuruh D Th< R#v Wm R Williams, STM, Ractet\n8:00 a.m.\u2014Holy Communion\n8:16 a.m.\u2014Family Service and Church Bchool\n11:00 a.m.\u2014Momlnv Prayer and Sermon\ntx XUALI AC 1 18ib Street Between F an* One\ndie I nU/VlAj Near Onoent Circle\n800 a.m. \u2014Holy Communion 11 :00 a.m. \u2014Sunday School\n11 e.m.\u2014MORNING PRAYER. SERMON by the Rev. Ceqen\nFrederick H. Artarton, D.D., of the Washington Cathedral\nREADING OF THE PRESIDENT'S THANKSGIVING\nTHANKSGIVING PROCLAMATION Spe^OW\n(Nursery in Parish House)\n7:30 p.m.\u2014Young Adults, Perish House 11 e.m,\nNORTHEAST\n(@ur Samnur 3SSKEL\n1818 Irel